parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Caliper Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake calipers can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS light illuminates
the brakes overheat
the brake pads and rotors wear out excessively
and the brake fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Master Cylinder Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake fluid leaks
and the ABS light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Hydraulic System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake fluid leaks
and the ABS light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain recall repairs can cause the brake failure to persist, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The owner receives a recall notice but is unable to obtain the necessary repairs due to parts unavailability or manufacturer delays.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall suddenly without warning, leading to a loss of power brakes and steering, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts down while driving
the engine stalls without warning
the power brakes and steering become unreliable
the accelerator goes to the floor
the engine can be restarted after a short period
the problem occurs intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the braking system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Burning smell from the brakes and wheel bearings
oil leaking from the wheel bearing covering the tire
inability to stop the vehicle
and the check engine light illuminating.
